    "text": "🎙️I was my pleasure to host the 🐍 Python Organizers' Panel at EuroPython 2023\n\n👉 Did you know that 🐍 Python conferences are run by volunteers🙋? Or I - how like to phrase it - run by experts 🤓 for other experts or experts to be. \n\nEuroPython is the annual gathering of the European 🐍 community and a great place to connect with other organizers to exchange experiences.\n\nIn a one-hour fireside chat we provided an engaging, authentic insight in our work as organizers to the audience.\n\n🏃 Our motivation and what drives us? - Contribute and foster a diverse community that enables exchange of knowledge and ideas.\n😅🫠 Challenges of being an organizer - Overload, recruiting new organizers, documentation, over -engineering and other obstacles in operation\n😂❤️‍🩹🤩 We also shared our funniest, most inspiring or heartbreaking anecdotes as community organizers.\n🌱💪Learnings being an organizer? - Better teamplay, work with and respect people from very different backgrounds, communication and leadership. \n\nThanks to 👩🏻‍💻 Alessia Marcolini (PyCon Italia), Jimena Bermúdez (PyCon Spain), Bára Drbohlavová, Honza Javorek (PyCon CZ) Tim (文昌) (PyCon APAC) and David Vaz (DjangoCon Europe) for for their participation in the panel discussion and their support in spreading our message to a wider audience.\n\nThanks to Paolo Melchiorre for the pictures.",
